  {
    "id": "98927409",
    "title": "Open Platform (Zumstein V4)",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/98927409",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 4,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-12-20T09:26:36.194Z",
    "text": "Stay up-to-date with our open platform APIs on platform.secutix.com (http://platform.secutix.com) \n 1 h2 rich content \n\n## Keys - API Monitoring: find errors in call details screen \n On your API monitoring screen, you can now filter down by response type in the details of an item (combination Key/Method) to only display the calls in error. This will help you with your analysis and issue resolution. \n\n For more info on our API Monitoring tool Keys, please check this page (https://confluence.secutix.com/display/DOCEN/How+to+use+the+API+Monitoring+tool%3A+Keys) \n\n## Keys - API Monitoring - refine time filters \n On your API monitoring screen, you can now click on the bar of the graph to narrow the time filters down do that time period. \n\n For more info on our API Monitoring tool Keys, please check this page (https://confluence.secutix.com/display/DOCEN/How+to+use+the+API+Monitoring+tool%3A+Keys)",
    "content_size": 1790,
    "text_size": 904
  },
