  {
    "id": "98926593",
    "title": "S-360 Zumstein V4",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/98926593",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 2,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-12-20T09:20:41.177Z",
    "text": "## S-360 \n## Zumstein V4 Release Notes \n\n #f3f3f3 \n Zumstein V4 will bring new and exciting features between August and November 2024. \n\n## Module \n## Highlights of the Rimpy V4 Release \n Online Sales \n\n Onsite Sales \n\n Engagement \n\n Back-office \n\n Open Platform \n\n## Full list of improvements per release",
    "content_size": 5595,
    "text_size": 305
  },
  {
    "id": "86278145",
    "title": "Installation calendar 2024",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/86278145",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 1,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-29T12:20:11.183Z",
    "text": "This page lists the calendar for the deliveries foreseen by SecuTix in 2024 . Please note that the plan is reviewed monthly, and is subject to modifications.",
    "content_size": 766,
    "text_size": 157
  },
  {
    "id": "76876063",
    "title": "Zumstein V3.12",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/76876063",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 8,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-22T09:00:34.807Z",
    "text": "## New SEPA version \n You can now use the SEPA 2019 version for all the SEPA related payment methods. We keep maintaining the older SEPA versions. \n## New version of Firefox Kit (https://app.getbeamer.com/secutix/en/new-firefox-kit-available-update-required) \n We would like to remind you that the new SECUTIX Firefox kit is has been available from the summer and can be downloaded here (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/43058553/SECUTIX+Firefox+Kit?utm_campaign=Firefox_Communication&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Firefox_Communication&utm_content=Firefox_Communication) . It includes the latest versions of Firefox ESR and Java which will give you many benefits such as the latest security updates and optimized Firefox core in order to speed up data loading and onscreen display. \n Read more (https://app.getbeamer.com/secutix/en/new-firefox-kit-available-update-required) \n## Improved data privacy for Friends & Family feature \n Aa a general principle, data privacy legislations impose that a person only sees the personal data he needs to carry out his tasks. Applied to the Friends & Family feature, this means that the group lead should only see the information needed to carry out his tasks, like paying the group member's reservation. Several small adaptations have been brought to the content of Ticket Shop pages to stick more tightly to this data privacy principle. \n## France: new requirements on invoices on January 1st \n Starting on January 1st, 2025, invoices in France will have to mention the SIREN. Also, the shipping address must be displayed if different from the invoice address.",
    "content_size": 2470,
    "text_size": 1621
  },
  {
    "id": "74318126",
    "title": "S-PAY Zumstein V3 Highlights",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/74318126",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 3,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-22T08:55:49.273Z",
    "text": "## \n## Zumstein V3 Release Notes \n\n 33% \n Payments methods \n\n solid \n## Saferpay - addition of TWINT as a payment method \n We added Twint as a payment method for our Swiss customers using Saferpay. \n\n## S-PAY - addition\u00a0 of VIPPS as a payment method \n We added VIPPS as a new available payment method in our payment solution, S-PAY, for our Nordics customers \n\n 33% \n## Payment solutions \n\n## Lottery load handling \n We can now handle a higher load during the lottery phase when capturing card payments. \n\n## Credit card authorisation \n We added the possibility to customise the amount of the authorisation for for credit card authorisations.",
    "content_size": 3866,
    "text_size": 642
  },
  {
    "id": "74318059",
    "title": "S-MOBILE Zumstein V3 Highlights",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/74318059",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 4,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-22T09:26:31.628Z",
    "text": "## \n## Zumstein V3 Release Notes Highlights \n\n## Major features \n\n solid \n## Revamped ticket resale (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49218116/Revamped+Ticket+Resale) \n Organisers currently manage ticket resale through organizer settings and transfer rules, which display the \"Resell your ticket\" button, even when no active resale platform is available on the S-360 side. To streamline on-site operations and align with the new \"Ticket Exchange\" feature, we are pleased to simplify the management of Resale configurations. This enhancement not only improves the user experience for organizers but also for spectators, ensuring a consistent and efficient process. \n\n## Ticket exchange (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217980/Ticket+Exchange) \n Organisers currently handle ticket exchanges outside of TIXNGO, relying on the S-360 back-office and ticketshop, which results in a manual and fragmented process. To streamline on-site operations, enhance the user experience, and provide spectators with more flexibility and autonomy, we\u2019re integrating this functionality into TIXNGO. This enhancement will not only simplify management but also unlock new revenue opportunities. \n\n 20% \n## Back-office \n\n 80% \n## Ticket list improvements (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217594/Back-Office+2024+Zumstein+V3#Back-Office(2024ZumsteinV3)-TicketsListimprovements) \n We\u2019ve made substantial improvements to the Tickets List screen to enhance your experience and streamline daily operations. \n## Spectators list improvements (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217594/Back-Office+2024+Zumstein+V3#Back-Office(2024ZumsteinV3)-SpectatorsListimprovements) \n We've made significant enhancements to the search functionality on the Spectators list screen. \n## Event search control improvements (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217594/Back-Office+2024+Zumstein+V3#Back-Office(2024ZumsteinV3)-Eventsearchcontrolimprovements) \n \"Event Search\" control was reshaped in order to bring more clarity and ease event selection across all TIXNGO Back-Office screen. \n## Back-office improvements (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217594/Back-Office+2024+Zumstein+V3#Back-Office(2024ZumsteinV3)-Variousback-officeimprovements) \n In our ongoing efforts to tidy up and simplify the back-office, we reorganised the back-office navigation and made some usability improvements. \n\n 20% \n## Mobile \n\n 80% \n## Change transfer recipient (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217605/Mobile+2024+Zumstein+V3#Mobile(2024ZumsteinV3)-Changetransferrecipient) \n In this release, we're happy to introduce a new feature that enhances the ticket transfer process. Mobile Wallet owners now have the ability to easily update the recipient's email address directly from the transfer pending screen. This improvement addresses common scenarios such as input errors or when the current recipient is unable to receive the tickets, streamlining the transfer workflow and avoiding the need to cancel and restart the process. \n## New UX for other Mobile App screens (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217605/Mobile+2024+Zumstein+V3#Mobile(2024ZumsteinV3)-NewUXforotherMobileAppscreens) \n\n In our ongoing mission to enhance the user experience on our Mobile Wallet, we are excited to announce that we support more screens on the new UX. \n## New ticket layout for TIXNGO V4 (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217887/New+ticket+layout+for+TIXNGO+V4) \n To demonstrate what's possible with TIXNGO v4, we are excited to introduce the new \"Ticket Details\" layout named Curiosity. \n This layout utilizes standardised TIXNGO v4 properties, including purchase and seating details, to enhance usability within the app.",
    "content_size": 7894,
    "text_size": 3893
  },
  {
    "id": "74318011",
    "title": "S-360 Zumstein V3 Highlights",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/74318011",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 10,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-22T10:12:36.919Z",
    "text": "## \n## Zumstein V3 Release Notes Highlights \n UK&IRL, NEU, DACH, FR, SP, US, LATAM \n\n 33% \n## Online Sales \n\n solid \n## New lottery module (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/43059482/New+lottery+module+Lottery+2.0) \n With our experience of running lottery process on many high profile occasions, we have reworked the front-end from scratch to provide a mobile first experience with a brand streamlined look & feel. On the back-end side, we have changed the data base for increased performance and reworked the draw process to remove all the pain points, in order to ensure seamless operations.\u00a0On top of that, we have added to capability of capturing the credit card information during the application phase so that winners can be automatically charged, both limiting the amount of fraudulent application while also optimizing the conversion rate. \n\n solid \n## Email validation at registration (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/43059867/Email+validation+at+registration+CR+540) \n Email validation at registration is a common feature of e-Commerce web and mobile sites. \n Any newly registered user has to confirm the email he entered is valid, usually by clicking on a confirmation link in a mail received on the provided email address. \n\n## New PeakProtect queue look & feel (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/43059150/New+PeakProtect+look+feel) \n A majority of online sales are now done using a mobile device. PeakProtect's brand-new mobile-responsive look & feel is there to provide a great first impression, regardless of the device. \n\n## SSO: automatic linking of accounts \n External SSO solutions do not require any manual linking by the user anymore. IDP are trusted to provide an email validation process and any existing user account will now be automatically linked to upon successful authentication. \n\n## Improved data privacy for Friends & Family feature (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/56001723/Improved+data+privacy+for+Friends+Family+feature) \n Aa a general principle, data privacy legislations impose that a person only sees the personal data he needs to carry out his tasks. Applied to the Friends & Family feature, this means that the group lead should only see the information needed to carry out his tasks, like paying the group member's reservation. Several small adaptations have been brought to the content of Ticket Shop pages to stick more tightly to this data privacy principle. \n\n 33% \n## Back-office \n\n## Compute tariff prices as a discount from another tariff (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/43059869/Compute+tariff+prices+as+a+discount+from+another+tariff) \n Some customers are defining child rates or season ticket holder rates as a percentage of a full rate. For example, the amount of the child tariff could match the full tariff with a discount of 40% (or 10\u20ac). \n Currently only \"no discount\" or \"fixed discounts\" can be defined for a tariff \n This feature adds a new discount possibility: tariff as a percentage of another tariff \n\n## New SEPA version (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/66225618/New+SEPA+version) \n You can now use the SEPA 2019 version for all the SEPA related payment methods. We keep maintaining the older SEPA versions. \n\n## New Stand-Alone Device Hub Manager (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/58982401/New+Stand-Alone+Device+Hub+Manager) \n We are rolling out a new stand-alone device hub manager that will replace the Firefox Kit. The main advantage is that the device manager is not packaged along with a specific version of Firefox ESR and you can now choose to use and keep up with the latest version of Firefox, even none ESR versions. \n\n## Operator import/export (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/55410691/Operator+import+export) \n Your list of operators can now be easily exported and imported between environments or organizations. The import file (JSON) can also be edited to create bulk import for new operators. \n\n## Security - Removed Support user capability for SSO accounts (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/43059652/Security+-+Removed+Support+user+capability+for+SSO+accounts+STX+143391) \n There is currently a Support user mode in which an operator can act in the context of any individual user as described on this page : How to use the Support mode? (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=43058723) \n It has been discovered that using a SSO account, i.e. an account managed by an external Identity Provider (IDP), as a Support account creates a significant security risk. \n\n## Addition of columns in report domains \n For the datamarts, the product creation date and time has been added to the D_CONFIG_PROD_LIST_V1_0 table, and the date of last update of the entry for the table D_SALES_LIST_SALES_V1_0. \n\n## France: new requirements on invoices on January 1st (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/73072664/France+new+requirements+on+invoices+on+January+1st+2025) \n Starting on January 1st, 2025, invoices in France will have to mention the SIREN. Also, the shipping address must be displayed if different from the invoice address. \n\n 50% \n## Open API \n\n## Keys - API Monitoring: find errors in call details screen \n On your API monitoring screen, you can now filter down by response type in the details of an item (combination Key/Method) to only display the calls in error. This will help you with your analysis and issue resolution. \n\n For more info on our API Monitoring tool Keys, please check this page (https://confluence.secutix.com/display/DOCEN/How+to+use+the+API+Monitoring+tool%3A+Keys) \n\n## Keys - API Monitoring - refine time filters \n On your API monitoring screen, you can now click on the bar of the graph to narrow the time filters down do that time period. \n\n For more info on our API Monitoring tool Keys, please check this page (https://confluence.secutix.com/display/DOCEN/How+to+use+the+API+Monitoring+tool%3A+Keys) \n\n <",
    "content_size": 13975,
    "text_size": 6064
  },
  {
    "id": "74317905",
    "title": "SECUTIX Zumstein V3",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/74317905",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 6,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-22T10:10:59.675Z",
    "text": "## \n## Zumstein V3 Release Notes Highlights \n\n 20 \n (https://confluence.secutix.com/wiki/display/RN/S-360+Zumstein+V1) \n\n 20% \n (https://confluence.secutix.com/wiki/display/RN/S-MOBILE+Zumstein+V1) \n\n 20% \n\n 20 \n## Email validation at registration (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/43059867/Email+validation+at+registration+CR+540) \n Email validation at registration is a common feature of e-Commerce web and mobile sites. \n Any newly registered user has to confirm the email he entered is valid, usually by clicking on a confirmation link in a mail received on the provided email address. \n\n turquoise large More on S-360 https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/74318011/S-360+Zumstein+V3+Highlights+Highlights \n\n 20% \n## Ticket exchange (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217980/Ticket+Exchange) management through TIXNGO (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/TIXNGO/pages/49217980/Ticket+Exchange) \n Organizers currently handle ticket exchanges outside of TIXNGO, relying on the S-360 back-office and ticketshop, which results in a manual and fragmented process. To streamline on-site operations, enhance the user experience, and provide spectators with more flexibility and autonomy, we\u2019re integrating this functionality into TIXNGO. This enhancement will not only simplify management but also unlock new revenue opportunities. \n\n turquoise large More on S-MOBILE https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/74318059/S-MOBILE+Zumstein+V3+Highlights \n\n 20% \n## New payment methods (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/74318126/S-PAY+Zumstein+V3+Highlights) \n As we are striving to follow the needs of our various markets, we are adding new payment methods to our payment solutions, whether it's Twint for Switzerland or Vipps for the Nordics. \n\n turquoise large More on S-PAY https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/74318126/S-PAY+Zumstein+V3+Highlights",
    "content_size": 7221,
    "text_size": 1974
  },
  {
    "id": "73072664",
    "title": "France: new requirements on invoices on January 1st, 2025",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/73072664",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 9,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-22T07:59:59.449Z",
    "text": "INLINE \n Starting on January 1st, 2025, invoices in France will have to mention the SIREN. Also, the shipping address must be displayed if different from the invoice address. \n## Solution \n SIREN and shipping address information are available in following documents: \n\n Order receipt \n\n Order summary \n\n File summary \n\n Invoice \n## SIREN number \n## Set-up the value of the SIREN \n The operator has to set the SIREN in the organization's administrative numbers \n## Display the SIREN on documents \n Order receipt \n Add following instruction at the place you would like to display the SIREN: \n #if($orderReceipt.siren.length() > 0)#space(5)SIREN CODE : #display($orderReceipt.siren, 22, 'LEFT')#end \n Order summary, file summary and invoice \n Add following instruction at the place you would like to display the SIREN: \n {#if($document.organization.legalInformation.get(\"ADMIN_NUM/SIREN\")) \n }{SIREN code: $document.organization.legalInformation.get(\"ADMIN_NUM/SIREN\")}{#end} \n## Shipment contact address \n Please contact our support if you have to add the shipment contact address to your documents. \n## Getting started \n Almost all our customers are using customized document templates. As a result, our customers will have to perform the updates to their templates. Don't hesitate to contact our support if you need some help.",
    "content_size": 2081,
    "text_size": 1326
  },
  {
