  {
    "id": "684916737",
    "title": "Two factor authentication for Backoffice operators - Video Demos",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/684916737",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 1,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-02-11T16:57:19.564Z",
    "text": "INLINE \n In order to increase the security and better control the access to your data, you can now enable a two factor authentication for your operators \n## MFA for Backoffice Operators using Mobile Phone \n This short video will cover the basic 2 factor authentication using a mobile phone \n\n## MFA for Backoffice Operators using 3rd party TOTP generator - KeePass (without using a mobile phone) \n This video will cover the basic 2 factor authentication using 3 rd party TOTP generator KeePass (without using a mobile phone). \n\n Improve security and data protection \n Starting March 1, 2026, enabling Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) will become mandatory.\u00a0After this date, access to the platforms will only be possible for users with MFA enabled. \n Of course, your operators need to be informed about the registration and login process.",
    "content_size": 2801,
    "text_size": 838
  },
  {
    "id": "66258457",
    "title": "Internal: new SEPA version configuration",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/66258457",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 3,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-11T10:57:32.226Z",
    "text": "To enable the new SEPA version for purchase orders with payment methods direct debit and bank withdrawals, use the Bank file generator institution parameter in Elcadmin. \n The parameter Bank file generator will be SEPA/ debit / credit , with the following details: \n\n SEPA is the prefix \n\n Debit accepted values: 02 (default), 03, TP2, 08 ( new ) \n\n Credit accepted values: 03 (default), 04, TP3, 09 ( new ). \n If the parameter value is only SEPA, the system will use 02 for the debit file and 03 for the credit file \n Examples: \n The customer want to use the old SEPA version: \n Bank file generator = SEPA OR Bank file generator = SEPA/02/03 \n The customer want to use the new SEPA version for debit and credit: \n Bank file generator: SEPA/08/09",
    "content_size": 1046,
    "text_size": 746
  },
  {
    "id": "66225618",
    "title": "New SEPA version",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/66225618",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 9,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2025-10-10T17:30:50.656Z",
    "text": "You can now use the SEPA 2019 version for all the SEPA related payment methods. We keep maintaining the older SEPA versions. \n## Activation \n To activate the new SEPA version, please verify the payment method type you use. \n## Payment method type withdrawal \n Please contact your customer success manager to enable the 2019 SEPA version. After this activation you won\u2019t have any other thing to do: the bank files generated will be of the new version. \n## Payment method type direct debit \n We introduced a new custom parameter in the Instalment management batch. This parameter is named sepaBankFileVersion and accept values SEPA_02 or SEPA_08. \n\n If the value of the new parameter is SEPA_02 , the file will be generated in the pain.008.001.02 format (old SEPA version) \n\n If the value of the new parameter is SEPA_08 , the file will be generated in the pain.008.001.08 format (the new SEPA version) \n\n If the custom parameter is not set or if its value is neither SEPA_08 nor SEPA_02, the file generated will be in the pain.008.001.02 format (old SEPA version). \n## Supplementary data [OPTIONAL] \n In this new version, your bank can publish data to be added to the bank files called supplementray data. This is optional for the bank, but mandatory for you to comply if the bank decides to publish some supplementary data. Please see with your banking institution for this supplementary data. \n The supplementary data will always follow the schema: wide 760 \n To handle supplementary data, we added a new administrative number field. The value needs to follow the following format: \n Text1;TagName:Text2 \n\n Example \n The supplementary data schema published by the bank is: wide 760 \n Then the supplementary data field in the administrative number should be : \n To maximize the export capabilities of this file, the special characters has been removed form this SEPA file format.",
    "content_size": 3593,
    "text_size": 1879
  },
  {
    "id": "643399681",
    "title": "Partial refund of memberships",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/643399681",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 1,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-02-02T16:26:37.821Z",
    "text": "UPCOMING Blue Selling membership subscriptions that may be cancelled before the end of their validity? A partial refund of the membership\u2019s value can now be done based on the remaining validity. \n## Solution \n Memberships with a validity running for an entire season may have to be partially refunded for compliance reasons. Operators can set a new validity end date to a membership in order to trigger the refund of the remaining value. The membership itself is not cancelled as it has been used for a certain period and may remain valid until the new end validity date, but an accounting product is created to refund the remaining value on a pro-rata basis. \n## Getting started \n Coming soon\u2026",
    "content_size": 1357,
    "text_size": 694
  },
  {
    "id": "641433602",
    "title": "Price breakdowns per currency",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/641433602",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 1,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-02-02T16:15:30.919Z",
    "text": "UPCOMING Blue Are you operating in a multi-currency context with rate tables per currency? Price breakdowns can now be defined separately for each currency. \n## Solution \n Multi-currency rate tables allow defining a specific price breakdown for each currency, so that prices for a sales channel supporting a specific currency can now be broken down into price components specific to that currency. \n## Getting started \n Coming soon\u2026",
    "content_size": 1089,
    "text_size": 432
  },
  {
    "id": "639893507",
    "title": "Distribution address book improvements",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/639893507",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 1,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-02-02T16:08:00.498Z",
    "text": "UPCOMING Blue The address book of the distribution portal will be automatically populated with contacts listed in the Excel file used in the bulk distribution. The UX of the address book has also been improved to help you find contacts faster. \n## Solution \n When uploading an Excel file to distribute tickets in bulk, the contacts listed in the Excel are automatically added to the sender\u2019s address book. Those address book contacts can then be used in the distribution cart, in the same way as contact created manually. \n The address book search pop-up has also been improved to make even faster to add to the distribution cart. \n## Getting started \n Coming soon\u2026",
    "content_size": 1356,
    "text_size": 665
  },
  {
    "id": "597557312",
    "title": "Adyen ApplePay for all browsers",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/597557312",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 3,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-02-02T15:28:24.883Z",
    "text": "RELEASED IN V1.1 Green You would like your clients using chrome browser to be able to pay with Apple Pay? It is now possible \n## Solution \n The ApplePay payment method is now supported in Chrome browsers. \n## Getting started \n The ApplePay QR code is displayed correctly in Chrome browsers and can be scanned on an iPhone to process easily the ApplePay payment.",
    "content_size": 2222,
    "text_size": 361
  },
  {
    "id": "59342849",
    "title": "Zumstein V3.9",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/59342849",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 1,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-10-25T15:10:32.404Z",
    "text": "## Export and import operators \n Your list of operators can now be easily exported and imported between environments or organizations. The import file (JSON) can also be edited to create bulk import for new operators. \n\n## Addition of columns in report domains \n For the datamarts, the product creation date and time has been added to the D_CONFIG_PROD_LIST_V1_0 table, and the date of last update of the entry for the table D_SALES_LIST_SALES_V1_0.",
    "content_size": 841,
    "text_size": 449
  },
  {
    "id": "592019457",
    "title": "Installation calendar 2025",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/592019457",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 1,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-01-19T12:24:50.340Z",
    "text": "This page lists the calendar for the deliveries foreseen by SecuTix in 2025 . Please note that the plan is reviewed monthly, and is subject to modifications. \n Deliveries are distinguished in feature patches ( Major deliveries ) and bug fixing patches ( Minor deliveries ). Feature patches bring new features and bug corrections in the systems, and follow the schedule of 2 weeks with Sprint pattern, while bug fixing patches contain exclusive corrections for bugs only. \n Deliveries are made available for all customers at the same time. However, some exceptions can occur for specific clouds . Please consult the SecuTix login window (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/download/attachments/43071153/login.png?version=1&modificationDate=1666411301032&cacheVersion=1&api=v2) to know which cloud you belong to. \n\n To consult the details of a patch already installed, click on the version number. It is also possible to consult the complete list of past releases here . \n Old deliveries can also be consulted here: Installation calendar 2024 .",
    "content_size": 4556,
    "text_size": 1046
  },
  {
    "id": "58982401",
    "title": "New Stand-Alone Device Hub Manager",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/58982401",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 24,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2025-07-28T14:42:33.613Z",
    "text": "INLINE \n We are rolling out a new stand-alone device hub manager that will replace the Firefox Kit. The main advantage is that the device manager is not packaged along with a specific version of Firefox ESR and you can now choose to use and keep up with the latest version of Firefox, even none ESR versions. \n## Solution \n The Device Hub Manager has been rebuilt to allow for an independent installation, which will work with any Firefox version and in particular the latest. This change provides a much simpler and secure deployment of Firefox and ensures that you can easily keep up with the latest version of Firefox, e.g., with automatic updates. \n## Getting started \n Make sure you have installed the latest version of Firefox before installing the new Device Manager Hub, with this solution you become the owner of the browser use and setting to access to S-360. \n## Installing the Device Hub Manager \n\n Download the Device Hub Manager installer from the specified location to your local computer. \n Device Hub Manager (https://engineering.secutix.com/firefox-kit/DeviceHubManager-1.1.6.msi) | MD5 (https://engineering.secutix.com/firefox-kit/DeviceHubManager-1.1.6.msi.md5) - f3e5c5219a7a407a702020bc51f9a9ab \n\n Run the installer from your local computer with administrative rights. \n\n Confirm the Microsoft UAC prompt when it appears to start the installation. \n The installer will create a folder at the following location \n```\n C:\\Program Files\\DeviceHubManager \n```\n\n After the installation, Windows may in some cases require a computer restart. \n The previous kit can stay and you can remove it as soon as you or your operator are confident with the use of the new tool. \n## Testing the Device Hub Manager \n After the installation, the Device Hub Manager should start automatically. \n Here are items you can check to validate that the Device Hub Manager is running correctly. \n\n A purple SECUTIX icon should be displayed in the system tray. \n\n If it does not appear, you can manually start it from the installation folder ( \n```\n C:\\Program Files\\DeviceHubManager \n```\n ), by using the desktop shortcut or from the program list. \n\n A new SECUTIX certificate should be listed in the Firefox list of certificates. \n\n A new SECUTIX certificae should be listed in the System: \n\n Accessing the URL ( http://127.0.0.1:8558 (http://127.0.0.1:8558) ) should detect your workstation's name \n\n## Additional information and advice \n\n The Device Hub Manager will automatically start with windows staring. \n\n When the Device Hub Manager is running: \n\n Using standard Firefox will connect to the new Device Hub Manager \n\n Using Firefox Kit will also connect to the new Device Hub Manager \n If a critical issue arises and you need to revert to the old solution: \n\n Stop the Device Hub Manager by right-clicking the icon in the system tray and selecting \"Exit Application\". \n\n Start the old solution by launching the Firefox Kit. \n\n## If you have TVM \n The installation process is exactly the same. Just install the app and verify that it start automatically. \n## What installation topic you may face and what are the solutions ? \n\n Description \n Workaround / Solution \n Comment \n 1 \n For some old BOCA, after installing the Device Hub and print the first ticket, there is a message asking user to reboot the printer \n Reboot the BOCA printer (by turn off then turn on the printer) \n After applying the workaround, the issue will not happen. \n 2 \n\n Issue: The Device Hub Manager may not start after installation. \n\n Details: This occurs on workstations where Java is already installed and is being used by another application. \n\n End all Java processes in Task Manager. \n\n Manual restart Device Hub Manager \n\n If it\u2019s not start, then clear the Java cache by deleting the contents of the following folder: \n```\n C:\\Users\\Public\\secutix\\javacache \n```\n . \n\n Uninstall and reinstall the Device Hub Manager again. \n\n If it\u2019s not start, then try to restart machine \n\n This is a sporadic issue that only occurs the first time after installation. After applying the workaround, the Device Hub Manager will automatically start after rebooting \n 3 \n Issue: In some cases, the browser cannot connect to the Device Hub Manager. \n Root Cause: The problem is related to issues with the SSL certificate. \n Behavior: A red cross appears on the printer icon. \n\n Access https://127.0.0.1:8555/ (https://127.0.0.1:8555/) , accept the risk and continue. \n\n After accepting the risk, the connection to printers will work as normal, and the red cross will disappear from the printer icon. \n 4 \n With some specific Windows setting, sometimes the following message will be displayed when installing the Device Hub Manager \n Open the installer property and check the below checkbox \n After changing the property, install the tool as usual. \n 5 \n Screens are configured with below position: \n Encountered below issue with the public screen (public screen displayed far away) \n\n Swap the position of the screen to the right order \n And public screen will be displayed ok \n\n 6 \n Install Extension on Firefox standard in order to have public screen full-screen by default \n Method 1 \n\n Download extension in https://engineering.secutix.com/firefox-kit/secutix.360webext@secutix.com.xpi (https://engineering.secutix.com/firefox-kit/secutix.360webext@secutix.com.xpi) \n\n Go to Firefox > Menu > Add-ons and themes \n or about:addons \n\n Choose \u201cInstall Add-on from file\u201d \n\n Choose downloaded file from Step 1 \n\n Choose \u201cAdd\u201d \n\n Method 2 \n\n Download extension \n\n Double-click on the downloaded file \n\n Choose Firefox browser to open the file \n\n Choose \u201cAdd\u201d \n\n For some passbook templates, some texts field are not modifiabe. \n Follow this steps: \n\n Select another field and make any modification, then save and close the template \n\n Reopen the template, the issue will not appear anymore",
    "content_size": 16227,
    "text_size": 5851
  },
  {
    "id": "589463634",
    "title": "New reporting domain for ticket distribution history",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/589463634",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 11,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-02-02T16:30:43.831Z",
    "text": "released in v1.1 Green Need reporting capabilities on distributions, take-backs and transfers? The full distribution history data is now available in a new reporting domain. \n## Solution \n A new reporting domain is now available under the Ticket theme that provides the full distribution history data of each ticket. A record of the domain corresponds to one distribution event of a ticket, with the ticket number, sender and recipient contact, operator and timestamp. \n## Getting started \n This domain corresponds to the view D_TICKET_DISTRIB_HISTORY_V1_0 . The full details of the domain is provided in the reporting domain documentation: D_TICKET_DISTRIB_HISTORY_V1_0 (https://play.demo-pos.secutix.com/tnin/apiDocs/D_TICKET_DISTRIB_HISTORY?lang=en&v=1.0) \n Known Limitation \n In some season ticket configurations (e.g. calculated price or fixed seat season ticket), distribution events performed on parent tickets are not exposed in the Ticket Distribution History domain. This is due to the absence of a ticket identifier for these events, even though distribution and movement information is available.",
    "content_size": 2240,
    "text_size": 1108
  },
  {
    "id": "583729199",
    "title": "Reprint ticket to original mobile contact",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/583729199",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 11,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-01-30T08:15:02.373Z",
    "text": "RELEASED IN V1.1 Green Do you need to sometimes re-assign tickets to the original contact who received the tickets in TIXNGO in the first place, instead of the current owner? You can now easily achieve that in the reprint process. \n## Solution \n A new option is now available in the back-office to allow reprinting a mobile ticket and assigning it back to its original owner. The system will automatically retrieve the original mobile owner of each ticket and assign the tickets to the corresponding contact. \n## Getting start \n Who is the original mobile contact? \n The contact who received first the current ticket on the secure wallet (TIXNGO) of their phone. \n The system will only consider the current ticket being reprinted. It will not look through the ticket invalidation chain to find the contact who first received a ticket on the secure wallet. \n In sales module (Ticket List, File Details or Seat Map), you can select the option \u201cAssign to original mobile contact\u201d in the cultural contact field of the reprint pop-up. After confirming the reprint, the system will retrieve the original mobile contact of each ticket being reprinted and will assign the corresponding contact to each ticket. \n Note that this option is only available for TIXNGO tickets.",
    "content_size": 2687,
    "text_size": 1263
  },
  {
    "id": "568098817",
    "title": "S-360 Dent Blanche V1",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/568098817",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 7,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-02-02T15:29:01.734Z",
    "text": "spotlight com.atlassian.confluence.spotlight Spotlight medium var(--ds-background-accent-yellow-subtlest, #fef7c8) rounded split-image-right Release notes Dent Blanche V1 will bring new and exciting features between January 2026 and April 2026. var(--ds-text, #292A2E) false default default c10a2f07-1ce7-4217-917f-591633bc7c3d spotlight com.atlassian.confluence.spotlight Spotlight medium var(--ds-background-accent-yellow-subtlest, #fef7c8) rounded split-image-right Release notes Dent Blanche V1 will bring new and exciting features between January 2026 and April 2026. var(--ds-text, #292A2E) false default default c10a2f07-1ce7-4217-917f-591633bc7c3d \n\n## New features 1 true h3 rich content 0 \n## Minor improvements \n RELEASED IN V1.1 Green Automatic address book contact creation on bulk distribution via Excel file import \n Do you provide the new distribution portal to your sponsors or commercial affiliates? When distributing tickets using the Excel file import, the system will now automatically add entries to the distributor\u2019s address book for all cultural contacts listed in the file.",
    "content_size": 4717,
    "text_size": 1098
  },
  {
    "id": "566659038",
    "title": "AAA - Dent v1 - Release notes per Owner",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/566659038",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 38,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-02-05T11:12:25.503Z",
    "text": "## How to manage release notes \n As a business owner of the ticket, you are responsible to update your JIRA tickets with: \n\n Short Release notes \n\n Release note category (back-office, Online sales, ...) \n\n (If required to be explained further to users) Dedicated release note page (drop-down)\u00a0 AND add a link to \"Short release notes\" fields to the designated page if applicable. \n You will find those fields when you enter the JIRA ticket details with a click on \"edit\". \n Dedicated pages need to be provided on the week of the feature release. See the calendar for 2026 here (https://confluence.secutix.com/wiki/display/RN/Installation+calendar) . \n\n## Release notes Dent V1.3 \n Delivery date: \n Demo date: \n Publish RN date: \n\n## Release notes Dent V1.2 \n Delivery date: \n Demo date: \n Publish RN date: \n\n Epic \n PM \n Assignee \n Demo status \n Not required | TO DEMO Yellow | to MENTION Purple | Topic replanned Red \n RN Status \n Not required | to write remark Purple | to write detail Yellow | TO REVIEW Blue | READY Green | PUBLISHED Green | Topic replanned Red 1 \n S-360 2 \n STIX-15003 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n to write remark Purple \n We have updated the seat map for fixed seat season tickets (Fest Abo) to display specific colors for each seat category. This resolves the issue where all seats appeared in the default primary color, allowing users to visually distinguish between price tiers (e.g., Cat 1 vs. Cat 4) without needing to click on them. 3 \n STIX-9892 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n to write detail Yellow 4 \n STIX-4509 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n to write detail Yellow 5 \n STIX-15632 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-18005 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n 6 \n STIX-13137 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red \n TO DEMO Yellow \n Topic replanned Red \n to write detail Yellow 7 \n STIX-15631 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TBD 8 \n STIX-4548 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n to write detail Yellow 9 \n STIX-18034 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n to MENTION Purple \n to write remark Purple 10 \n STIX-4487 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-18423 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-18424 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n TBD \n to write detail Yellow 11 \n STIX-19879 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n to MENTION Purple \n to write remark Purple 12 \n STIX-19858 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 13 \n STIX-12263 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 14 \n STIX-9420 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 15 \n STIX-19791 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n to write remark Purple 16 \n STIX-19735 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 17 \n STIX-19770 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 18 \n\n 19 \n S-PAY 20 \n STIX-14479 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n to write detail Yellow 21 \n STIX-19675 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 22 \n STIX-14513 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 23 \n STIX-10664 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 24 \n STIX-2844 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-18476 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red \n Topic replanned Red 25 \n\n 26 \n S-MOBILE 27 \n STIX-19209 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 28 \n STIX-15905 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n to MENTION Purple \n to write remark Purple 29 \n STIX-13074 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n to MENTION Purple \n to write remark Purple 30 \n STIX-15650 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n to write detail Yellow 31 \n STIX-18739 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 32 \n STIX-9850 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-17678 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-17679 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TBD \n to MENTION Purple \n to write remark Purple (S360 side) 33 \n STIX-4564 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-16804 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-17459 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n to MENTION Purple \n to write detail Yellow 34 \n STIX-15593 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-17221 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n to write remark Purple 35 \n STIX-4523 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-13110 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n STIX-16986 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 36 \n STIX-16835 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 37 \n\n Filter https://jira-secutix.atlassian.net/issues/?jql=type%20IN%20(Epic%2C%20%22User%20Story%22)%0AAND%20fixversion%20IN%20(%22Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2023.02.2026%22%2C%20%22Lottery%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2016.02.2026%22%2C%20%22OSS%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2016.02.2026%22%2C%20%22SPAY%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2016.02.2026%22%2C%20%22Widget%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2016.02.2026%22%2C%20%22TNG%20DeB%20V1%20Sprint%202%20%7C%2018.02.2026%22%2C%20%22SAM%22)%20AND%20%22team%5Bteam%5D%22%20IN%20(3917170a-05c3-4ab2-ab3d-4efb7fe773c9%2C%206fdb24d5-c519-42b1-b47c-15054c001981%2C%20ac2a66e0-8d75-4622-85d3-f437616e7926%2C%2043fa2f27-0508-40bf-aa49-dcf175c40ea5%2C%2082a2db35-e64b-49ae-bf7e-2d8f29eff288)%0AORDER%20BY%20type%20asc%2C%20Team%20asc%2C%20pm%20%20ASC%2C%20parent%2C%20status%20%2C%20Sub-team%2C%20Sprint%20DESC (https://jira-secutix.atlassian.net/issues/?jql=type%20IN%20(Epic%2C%20%22User%20Story%22)%0AAND%20fixversion%20IN%20(%22Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2023.02.2026%22%2C%20%22Lottery%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2016.02.2026%22%2C%20%22OSS%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2016.02.2026%22%2C%20%22SPAY%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2016.02.2026%22%2C%20%22Widget%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.2%20%7C%2016.02.2026%22%2C%20%22TNG%20DeB%20V1%20Sprint%202%20%7C%2018.02.2026%22%2C%20%22SAM%22)%20AND%20%22team%5Bteam%5D%22%20IN%20(3917170a-05c3-4ab2-ab3d-4efb7fe773c9%2C%206fdb24d5-c519-42b1-b47c-15054c001981%2C%20ac2a66e0-8d75-4622-85d3-f437616e7926%2C%2043fa2f27-0508-40bf-aa49-dcf175c40ea5%2C%2082a2db35-e64b-49ae-bf7e-2d8f29eff288)%0AORDER%20BY%20type%20asc%2C%20Team%20asc%2C%20pm%20%20ASC%2C%20parent%2C%20status%20%2C%20Sub-team%2C%20Sprint%20DESC) \n\n## Release notes Dent V1.1 \n Demo date: \n Publish RN date: \n\n Epic \n PM \n Assignee \n Demo status \n Not required | TO DEMO Yellow | to MENTION Purple | Topic replanned Red \n RN Status \n Not required | to write remark Purple | to write detail Yellow | TO REVIEW Blue | READY Green | PUBLISHED Green | Topic replanned Red 1 \n S-360 2 \n STIX-14627 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n PUBLISHED Green \n New reporting domain for ticket distribution history 3 \n STIX-15327 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n PUBLISHED Green New screenshot to add! \n https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/x/LwDLIg (https://go.confluence.secutix.com/wiki/x/LwDLIg) 4 \n STIX-17500 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n PUBLISHED Green \n Automatic address book contact creation on bulk distribution via Excel file import \n Do you provide the new distribution portal to your sponsors or commercial affiliates? When distributing tickets using the Excel file import, the system will now automatically add entries to the distributor\u2019s address book for all cultural contacts listed in the file. 5 \n STIX-15003 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red \n to write remark Purple Topic replanned Red \n We have updated the seat map for fixed seat season tickets (Fest Abo) to display specific colors for each seat category. This resolves the issue where all seats appeared in the default primary color, allowing users to visually distinguish between price tiers (e.g., Cat 1 vs. Cat 4) without needing to click on them. 6 \n STIX-18641 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 7 \n STIX-16966 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 8 \n STIX-15637 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n \u2192 STIX-18022 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n\n Not required 9 \n STIX-4488 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red \n TO REVIEW Blue Topic replanned Red \n Standard Mobile Ticketing 10 \n\n 11 \n S-PAY 12 \n STIX-14132 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n PUBLISHED Green \n Adyen ApplePay for all browsers 13 \n STIX-2843 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow \n PUBLISHED Green \n Bottomline improvements 14 \n STIX-10664 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red \n Topic replanned Red 15 \n STIX-2844 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red \n Topic replanned Red 16 \n STIX-13665 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red \n Topic replanned Red 17 \n STIX-9398 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 18 \n\n 19 \n S-MOBILE 20 \n STIX-16873 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n TO DEMO Yellow (1 demo for BO improvement) \n to write detail Yellow 21 \n STIX-4494 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 22 \n STIX-16044 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 23 \n STIX-19078 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 24 \n STIX-18913 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 25 \n STIX-13110 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red Not required \n Topic replanned Red \n to write remark Purple 26 \n STIX-17616 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 27 \n STIX-16835 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red Not required \n Topic replanned Red \n to write remark Purple 28 \n STIX-17595 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n to write remark Purple 29 \n STIX-16109 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 30 \n STIX-1482 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Not required \n Not required 31 \n STIX-15650 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red \n TO DEMO Yellow \n Topic replanned Red \n to write detail Yellow 32 \n STIX-17221 6991b051-361b-3402-ae85-bb72c8582d0b Jira \n\n Topic replanned Red TO DEMO Yellow (1 demo for BO improvement) \n Topic replanned Red to write remark Purple \n Filter https://jira-secutix.atlassian.net/issues/?jql=type%20IN%20(Epic%2C%20%22User%20Story%22)%0AAND%20fixversion%20IN%20(%22Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22Lottery%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22OSS%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22SAM%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2028.01.2026%22%2C%20%22SPAY%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22Widget%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22TNG%20DeB%20V1%20Sprint%201%20%20%7C%2004.02.2026%22)%20AND%20%22team%5Bteam%5D%22%20IN%20(3917170a-05c3-4ab2-ab3d-4efb7fe773c9%2C%206fdb24d5-c519-42b1-b47c-15054c001981%2C%20ac2a66e0-8d75-4622-85d3-f437616e7926%2C%2043fa2f27-0508-40bf-aa49-dcf175c40ea5%2C%2082a2db35-e64b-49ae-bf7e-2d8f29eff288)%0AORDER%20BY%20type%20asc%2C%20Team%20asc%2C%20pm%20%20ASC%2C%20parent%2C%20status%20%2C%20Sub-team%2C%20Sprint%20DESC (https://jira-secutix.atlassian.net/issues/?jql=type%20IN%20(Epic%2C%20%22User%20Story%22)%0AAND%20fixversion%20IN%20(%22Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22Lottery%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22OSS%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22SAM%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2028.01.2026%22%2C%20%22SPAY%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22Widget%20Dent%20Blanche%20V1.1%20%7C%2002.02.2026%22%2C%20%22TNG%20DeB%20V1%20Sprint%201%20%20%7C%2004.02.2026%22)%20AND%20%22team%5Bteam%5D%22%20IN%20(3917170a-05c3-4ab2-ab3d-4efb7fe773c9%2C%206fdb24d5-c519-42b1-b47c-15054c001981%2C%20ac2a66e0-8d75-4622-85d3-f437616e7926%2C%2043fa2f27-0508-40bf-aa49-dcf175c40ea5%2C%2082a2db35-e64b-49ae-bf7e-2d8f29eff288)%0AORDER%20BY%20type%20asc%2C%20Team%20asc%2C%20pm%20%20ASC%2C%20parent%2C%20status%20%2C%20Sub-team%2C%20Sprint%20DESC)",
