  {
    "id": "56001723",
    "title": "Improved data privacy for Friends & Family feature",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/56001723",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 18,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2024-11-13T09:09:12.945Z",
    "text": "INLINE \n Aa a general principle, data privacy legislations impose that a person only sees the personal data he needs to carry out his tasks. Applied to the Friends & Family feature, this means that the group lead should only see the information needed to carry out his tasks, like paying the group member's reservation. Several small adaptations have been brought to the content of Ticket Shop pages to stick more tightly to this data privacy principle. \n## Solution \n This section describes the group member's personal information that a group lead can't see anymore, even if the group member has given his consent. Note that an internet user will still see his own files and orders as before. \n## List of friends and family \n The group lead doesn't see anymore the email address of the group members. \n\n Although Becky Smith has given her consent to be a member of the group, the group lead doesn't see her email address. \n## Payment of a reservation performed by a group member \n## Selection of a delivery method \n When the group lead pays a reservation performed by a group member, he will be able to reuse the shipment mode selected by the group member during the reservation. \n\n In example above, the group lead simply reuses the postal shipment selected by the group member. This means that the tickets will be shipped to the group member without disclosing the group member's postal address to the group lead. The group lead may still decide to get the tickets by selecting another shipment mode. Only by selecting the first shipment mode displayed, the tickets will be shipped to the group member. \n## Order summary displayed during order finalisation (order payment) \n If the shipment contact (in our case: the group member) is different from the payer contact (in our case: the group lead), only the delivery method is displayed. \n\n## File summary and content (select a file from the order history) \n The Print file summary button has been removed from the File summary section to avoid the disclosure of personal data (for example postal address) displayed on the file summary document. \n\n The group lead will only see the delivery contact (first name and last name of the group member) but he won't see any email or postal address. \n## \n The button in the change history to print the order summary has been removed since the order summary displays some personal data like the postal address. \n## Removal/anonymization of group members that haven't given their consent \n S-360 now provides you the ability to clean up the contacts that haven't given their consent after a duration of your choice. To achieve this, a new option has been added to the already existing anonymisation batch, as illustrated below: \n\n The result of the anonymisation process is summarised in table below: Group lead has created contact Contact has logged in to his account since he received the consent email Group lead has booked or bought tickets on behalf of group member Result No (already existing contact) Not relevant Not relevant Remove contact from the group Yes (contact created by group lead) No (fully inactive) No (just added contact to his group) Delete contact \n No (fully inactive) Yes Reassign tickets in the future to the group lead and delete the contact \n Yes Not relevant Contact is kept as is \n## Getting started \n## Better filtering of information displayed to the group lead \n To benefit from these improvements, you have to set the configuration key config.friendsAndFamily.GDPR.hideGroupMemberInfo to true. \n\n This new behaviour will become mandatory during 2025! \n In order to cope with the Privacy by default principle required by many data privacy regulations, this new behaviour will become mandatory during 2025. More precisely, after delivery of release 2025 V2 (July 2025), this behaviour will be enabled by default with no way to disable it. \n## Removal/anonymization of group members that haven't given their consent \n To use this feature, create an additional schedule for the anonymisation batch using the parameters illustrated in section above.",
    "content_size": 6131,
    "text_size": 4072
  },
  {
    "id": "55410691",
    "title": "Operator & profile import/export",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/55410691",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 9,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2025-01-20T14:54:20.514Z",
    "text": "INLINE \n Need to create operators in bulk or copy them from other environments? Your list of operators and their profiles can now be easily exported and imported between environments or organizations. \n## Solution \n The list of operators screens now have import and export options to easily copy operators from one environment to another, e.g., between PROD and PREPROD, or from a different organization within your SECUTIX instance. The import file (JSON) can also be edited to create a bulk import file for new operators. \n## Getting started \n This function is available at institution and at organization level. In the organization and in the institution profiles screens, the following options are now available: \n\n Check box to select the profile to export \n\n Export button with Export all and Export selected options \n\n Import button \n\n## Profiles \n Select the profiles that you want to export and click on Export selected or Export all if you want to export all the lines. A JSON export file is generated and downloaded. \n Please note that the number of profile to export is limited to 1000 profiles. \n\n You can now import this file in the production environment or in the other institution you need to. Click on import and select your file. \n This file must not exceed 2MB. \n\n If a profile does not exist, it will be created by the import process. \n\n If a profile with the same code already exists, the privileges of that profile will be updated. \n Errors may occur if you are exporting/importing profiles between environments with different active security packages. If it is the case, please contact our support service. \n## Operators \n For operators, the process is almost the same: \n\n The feature is available at the institution and at the organization level. \n\n You can import selected operators or all of them. \n\n The limit in term of size of the file and number of operators are the same than for profiles (2MB and up to 1000 operators). \n For security reason the following information is excluded from the import and export functions: \n\n Operator Passwords \n\n MFA accounts \n\n Access Control Rights \n\n Virtual Operator \n When exporting the operators you will have to select the organization for which you want to export the data. \n\n If an operator exists in the system, the imported data will be merge with the existing data. This means that imported operators may get additional access rights, if their profiles exist in the target environment. In such cases, they will retain their previous rights and gain any new rights from the import.",
    "content_size": 4225,
    "text_size": 2555
  },
  {
    "id": "551583821",
    "title": "Enhanced contact data & security auditing",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/551583821",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 6,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-01-29T22:09:30.599Z",
    "text": "releaseD in v4.5 Green Operating in Italy or do you simply need to capture specific contact details - like place of birth - during your delivery or billing flows? We have expanded our data collection capabilities, allowing you to request place of birth and track origin IP addresses across more stages of the customer journey to meet your specific administrative or security needs. \n## Solution \n We have extended the availability of contact fields to support more comprehensive data collection across different forms. \n Extended Field Availability \n\n ID Type: Previously available for account creation, the ID Type field is now available in Shipment contact and Relay Sub-group forms. \n\n Place of Birth: You can now capture place of birth ( Country , Town , ...) in Billing contact forms, Shipment contact forms, Relay Sub-group forms, Friends & Family (purchase on behalf), and Individual purchase forms. \n Enhanced Security Auditing (IP Address) \n To support fraud detection and security auditing, the system now automatically captures the Origin IP Address : \n\n Registration: Records the source IP when a new account is created. \n\n Login: Persists the IP of the first login event in case it was not to recorded at creation ( for legacy accounts). \n## Get Started \n## Configuration \n In the screen configuration of the organization, you can now set place of birth and ID type to Optional or Mandatory for the Shipment , Billing and Relay forms.",
    "content_size": 4393,
    "text_size": 1447
  },
  {
    "id": "550076432",
    "title": "Payment terminal current transaction cancellation",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/550076432",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 10,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-01-09T08:36:56.231Z",
    "text": "RELEASED IN V4.5 Green An operator made a mistake in the order? They would like to cancel it but you find frustrating to have to use the cancel button in the TPE? \n This situation can be even more tricky if the operator does not have access to the TPE due to a physical separation of the operator and the TPE. Currently the only solution would be to ask the clients to click on the cancel button themselves. \n\n Thanks to this evolution, the operator will be able to cancel the payment on the terminal directly from s360 ! \n\n## Solution \n We now added a cancel button in the s360 buy flow that cancel the payment on the terminal \n\n## Getting started \n Please create a service case in order to ask for this feature to be activated",
    "content_size": 2094,
    "text_size": 728
  },
  {
    "id": "549584931",
    "title": "Standard Mobile Ticketing",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/549584931",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 3,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-01-08T08:43:39.645Z",
    "text": "Still delivering tickets as PDFs? \n Standard Mobile Ticketing (SMT) lets your customers access their tickets instantly on mobile, display QR codes right after purchase, share tickets securely, and add them to Apple or Google Wallet (through our partner N\u00e9ostore). All directly from your ticket shop. \n## Solution \n The solution consists in introducing a Standard Mobile Ticketing widget into the ticket shop, allows user to: \n\n Access to the tickets immediately after purchase, i.e confirmation page, to scan at access control or to share with friends. \n\n Transfer a ticket to a friend using a secure link, who can then easily display it without having to log in or even create an account \n\n That same secure link is provided in the confirmation email of the order to allow your customers to find their tickets later on and display them again without having to log in. \n\n Access the tickets later on in \"My tickets\" page \n## Supported features: \n## Standard Mobile Ticketing (SMT) \u2013 Supported Features \n Feature \n Conditions / Notes \n Supported \n SMT ticket display with QR code on: \n\n Order confirmation page \n\n My tickets page \n\n Order confirmation email. \n\n Shared link from other users. \n Controlled by POS parameter \u201cShow E-Ticket barcodes\u201d \n \u2705 \n Secure ticket sharing \n\n No login required for recipient \n\n One ticket per shared link \n\n Order confirmation email shares a ticket group \n \u2705 \n Shared link access \n\n Accessible from email or forwarded link \n\n No login required \n \u2705 \n Download ticket as PDF \n PDF file must be available in model variant setting. \n \u2705 \n Add to Apple Wallet /Google Wallet \n\n Requires N\u00e9ostore activation \n OR passbook file in ticket model (iOS only) \n \u2705 \n Upload URL image \n Supported in SMT ticket templates \n \u2705 \n SMT link with list of tickets in Order confirmation email. \n Variable in template: \n \u2705 \n Custom template variables \n Formula, math, and conditional logic \n Powered by Apache Velocity \n \u2705 \n Ticket resale \n Not supported \n \u274c \n Ticket upgrade / exchange \n Not supported \n \u274c \n\n## Getting started \n You can now activate Standard Mobile Ticketing (SMT) in a few simple steps: \n\n Configure the SMT with a new editor: \n\n Use the Digital Template at Institution level \n\n Customize the SMT ticket layout \n SMT Editor \n\n Assign the digital template to the ticket model \n\n Add the configured digital template to the relevant ticket model. \n\n Enable SMT display in Ticketshop: \n\n Enable Show E-ticket barcodes param in Sale channel > Pos parameters \n Supported product families (ALL) \n\n Single Entry \n\n Event \n\n Competition \n\n Composed Product: \n\n Package \n\n Season ticket \n\n Pass: \n\n Open pass \n\n Visit pass \n\n Timeslot pass \n\n Simple Product: \n\n Service \n\n Voucher (Financial/Experience) \n\n Donation \n\n Goods \n\n Membership \n\n Points of Attention: \n\n SMT focuses on ticket display and access , independently of shipment mode. \n\n Apple Wallet and Google Wallet require N\u00e9ostore activation . Without N\u00e9ostore, wallet support is limited to iOS devices using PASSBOOK file in Model Variant . \n\n To respect the consistent SMT layout, certain positions are fixed (Images, Product name, Site, Date/time, QR code, Terms). \n\n Recommended minimum screen width for optimal readability and QR code display: \n\n Mobile / tablet: \u2265 360 px \n\n Desktop: \u2265 1024 px",
    "content_size": 18791,
    "text_size": 3279
  },
  {
    "id": "545751041",
    "title": "Receipt for cash transactions (none sales)",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/545751041",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 9,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-01-27T11:09:08.958Z",
    "text": "releaseD in v4.6 Green Are you taking cash payments outside of standard sales, to credit or balance an account? You can now configure an automatic receipt or print a receipt on demand for past transactions. \n## Solution \n We have introduced a new Accounts transaction document type for cash payments that are not part of a regular sales, i.e., cash payments done for a pending account, credit balance, deposit, installment or bank agreement). \n Once configured, the receipt will be automatically printed for each successful cash transaction. The receipt can also be printed on demand later on for any paid transaction. \n## Getting started \n## Configuration \n The accounts transaction document type is available by default for all institutions. \n In Document to send , assign this Accounts transaction document type to the relevant sales channels. \n\n Sample receipt \n## Automatic printing \n Account transaction receipts are printed automatically after a successful cash payment, under the following conditions: \n\n An Accounts transaction document is configured in the Document to send for the sales channel, and \n\n The organization setting \u201c Print receipt only on request \u201d is set to \u201c no \u201d. \n\n The receipt will be printed for any cash payment done in the following screens \n\n Pending account \n\n Credit balance \n\n Deposit \n\n Installment \n\n Bank agreement \n## Manual print from Payment list \n In the Payment list screen, a receipt can be printed for any PAID payment by selecting the payment and clicking on the new Print receipt button.",
    "content_size": 6695,
    "text_size": 1535
  },
  {
