  {
    "id": "468090901",
    "title": "Flexible customization of robots.txt",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/468090901",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 6,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2025-12-12T04:47:18.744Z",
    "text": "INLINE \n Released in V4.4 Green Do you need more control over how search engines crawl your site? Whether it is for specific SEO strategies, Google Shopping feeds, or hiding sensitive catalog sections, you can now fully customize your \n```\n robots.txt \n```\n file. \n## Solution \n We have introduced a flexible mechanism to manage search engine indexing, moving away from the previously hard-coded file. This allows customers to define specific rules to allow or disallow bots, or to completely replace the default file with a custom one. This flexibility is essential for compliance with advertising strategies (e.g., allowing Googlebot-Image) and optimizing organic search traffic. \n We now offer two methods to configure your robots.txt, depending on your needs: \n 1. Additional Directives (Recommended for safety) You can inject additional rules (User-agent, Allow, Disallow, Sitemap) on top of the system defaults. \n\n Pros: The default security rules (blocking \n```\n /checkout/ \n```\n , \n```\n /account/ \n```\n ) remain intact. \n\n Behavior: Your new rules are validated and appended to the existing file. \n 2. Full File Override (Advanced) You can upload a completely custom \n```\n robots.txt \n```\n file via the theme configuration. \n\n Pros: Maximum flexibility; you have complete control over every line of the file. \n\n Behavior: If a valid file is found, it replaces the system default entirely. \n## Getting started \n To Append Rules: \n\n Config Key: \n```\n config.robots.additionalDirectives \n```\n\n Format: List of valid directives (User-agent, Allow, Disallow, Sitemap). \n\n Validation: Invalid syntax will be skipped with a warning log. \n To Full Override: \n\n File Location: \n```\n theme.robots.txt \n```\n\n Requirement: Must be a \n```\n .txt \n```\n file with UTF-8 encoding. \n Known Limitations & Constraints \n\n Override Risk: If you use the Full Override ( \n```\n theme.robots.txt \n```\n ), the system defaults are completely removed. You are responsible for manually adding protection for sensitive paths (e.g., \n```\n /checkout/ \n```\n , \n```\n /account/ \n```\n ) to prevent them from being indexed. \n\n Validation: In \"Append\" mode, if a directive contains invalid syntax, it is silently skipped (logged as a warning) rather than breaking the entire file. \n\n Conflict Resolution: You cannot use \"Append\" mode to remove a default rule; you can only add to them. If you need to remove a default rule, you must use the \"Full Override\" method.",
    "content_size": 6348,
    "text_size": 2433
  },
  {
    "id": "454983681",
    "title": "Click to pay custom email",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/454983681",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 3,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2025-12-12T09:01:43.919Z",
    "text": "Released in V4.4 Green Your client\u2019s email for click to pay is different than the one in their secutix account? We now support the possibility to register a new email in this case \n## Solution \n\n If the email registered in the secutix account exists on Click To Pay it is the one used : \n\n If the email does not exist on click to pay, we ask the customer the email he would like to use \n then the customer can continue the standard process for this payment method \n\n## Getting started \n\n This is the new default for all clients",
    "content_size": 2904,
    "text_size": 527
  },
  {
    "id": "450560001",
    "title": "Pre-configuration of installment dates",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/450560001",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 5,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2026-01-09T08:38:44.970Z",
    "text": "releaseD in v4.5 Green Do you allow your customers to pay by installments and want even more flexibility in the configuration of the dates? This improvement will allow you define easily when and how often the installments are due. \n## Solution \n The configuration of installment dates has been improved to allow operators to set up sales plans that better fit different financial requirements, with additional fixed dates and more flexible recurring installment definition. \n## Getting started \n In the configuration of the payment methods, the installment dates have the following new options: \n\n 1st installment - on a specific day : a specific day of the month (1\u201331) for the first installment. Note that if that day is in the past for the current month, the following month will be used. Example: assuming the day is set to the 15th, \n\n if the order is created before the 15th of the current month, the first installment will the 15th of the current month. \n\n if the order is created after the 15th of the current month, the first installment will be the 15th of the following month. \n\n 3rd installment on a fixed date : an absolute date for the 3rd installment. \n\n 4th installment on a fixed date : an absolute date for the 4th installment. \n\n Recurrence : the frequency of recurring installments, in days, weeks or months. \n\n Same as 1st installment day : the day of each subsequent installment (not individually defined) will match the first installment date. \n\n On specific day : a specific day of the month when each subsequent installment (not individually defined) is due. \n Note that recurrence configuration defines how additional installments are defined beyond the configuration of the first 4. However, the 2nd, 3rd and 4th installment dates are optional, meaning that beyond the first installment, others will follow the recurrence configuration. \n Additionally, the parameters for pending account have been regrouped under a dedicated tab. \n## Examples \n To define relative installment dates, only use the \u201c1st installment\u201d and the recurrence. For example, having a first installment due immediate and then all following installments due on the same day every month. \n To define absolute installment dates, use the 1st, 2nd, 3rd and 4th installment fix dates. Note that in this case, the configuration will have to be updated regularly with time passing.",
    "content_size": 5731,
    "text_size": 2372
  },
  {
    "id": "43075306",
    "title": "Facebook Domain Verification on a Ticketshop",
    "url": "https://confluence-secutix.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RN/pages/43075306",
    "status": "current",
    "version": 1,
    "created": "",
    "updated": "2022-07-04T07:35:21.302Z",
    "text": "If you need to do a Facebook Domain Verification, you have two possibilities: \n If the ticketshop is on your own domain , use the DNS method, by adding the needed value to your DNS \n If the ticketshop is on *.shop.secutix.com \n go to Organization \u2192 Initialization \u2192 Sales channels \u2192 your ticketshop \u2192 Points of sales \u2192 your point of sale \u2192 Theme \u2192 Advanced \n Create a new entry with key config.head.custom.tags , and put the value of the meta tag in it, like for example: \n\n```\n <meta name=\"facebook-domain-verification\" content=\"xxx\" /> \n```\n\n Wait 10 minutes, to be sure the key is synced to the Ticketshop \n Do the verification with Facebook \n Remove the meta key from the point of sales",
    "content_size": 873,
    "text_size": 690
  },
  {
